	<Title>
		Sunscreen shopping tips
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;When you&apos;re shopping for sunscreen, don&apos;t just grab the bottle with the highest SPF. A sunscreen with an SPF of at least 15 can be a good choice if it is also a broad-spectrum sunscreen, which means it protects against UVA and UVB rays. Also check the expiration date and whether the sunscreen is water resistant. Ultimately, it&apos;s important to choose a sunscreen you like. If you don&apos;t care for the sunscreen, you&apos;re not likely to use it.&lt;/p&gt;
